      • getBranchPath

        IBranchPath getBranchPath(java.lang.String repositoryId)
        Returns the branch path for the specified repository UUID.

        May return either null or MAIN if the repository did not have any branch path set or the branch path is not known.

        Parameters:
        repositoryId - the repository UUID to look up
        Returns:
        the associated branch path

      • getBranchPath

      • asMap

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,IBranchPath> asMap(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> repositoryIds)
        Returns a Map view of this IBranchPathMap with the supplied keys. An attempt will be made to create entries for all keys in the given repository identifier key set.
        Parameters:
        repositoryIds - the key set to populate when creating the map
        Returns:
        a map containing all entries of an IBranchPathMap, regardless of where the entry has been set (on this instance or any ancestor)

      • getLockedEntries

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,IBranchPath> getLockedEntries()
        Returns:
        a map containing entries on this IBranchPathMap instance which are not allowed to change, or an empty map if no such entries can be found
